## Suggested fix priority (if/when changes are made)

1. **#1** (high) — hook `node` PATH resolver; silently breaks the core feature on nvm. Same fix class already shipped for statusline.
2. **#3 + #16** (medium) — fire-and-forget vector ops lost on exit; add `flushEmbeddings()` + boot backfill. Fixes a permanent silent vector-index hole.
3. **#6, #11, #29, #30, #31** (docs) — doc/code drift batch; cheap, prevents false user expectations.
4. **#2** (medium, one-liner) — `store.ts` sessions cap.
5. **#9, #27** (infra) — `install.sh` `--vector` save flag + standalone hook command shape.
6. **#5, #7, #8, #24, #25, #26** (tests) — close coverage gaps on security-critical hooks, hybrid RRF, LRU TTL, hookEventName, sessions cap, integration invariants.
7. **#4, #17, #18, #19, #20, #21, #22, #23** (perf) — mostly low-impact micro-optimizations; #4 (read-triggered IDF rebuild) and #18 (dead boot load) are the most worthwhile.
8. **#10, #12, #13, #14, #15, #28** (low) — minor correctness/security/observability edge cases.

